nfsroot (0.5) unstable; urgency=low

  * Improved  checking for double HW addresses/IP numbers, and
    added option to write such changes to syslog.
  * The example kernel provided didn't work
  * created manual pages for mknfsroot and nrpobenet.
  * mknfsroot now copies symlinks in /etc directly to
    /tftpboot/$ip/etc/..., instead of links into /remote-etc/...
  * fixed typo in boot script.
 -- joost witteveen <joost@rulcmc.leidenuniv.nl>  Sat, 3 May 1997 14:55:28 +0200

nfsroot (0.4) unstable; urgency=low

  * added another sanity check in mknfsroot
  * recompiled for libg++-2.7.2.1 (you need at least this version to run it)
  
 -- joost witteveen <joost@rulcmc.leidenuniv.nl>  Tue, 12 Nov 1996 23:46:06 +0100

nfsroot (0.3) unstable; urgency=low

  * added extra test for /etc/nfsroot/$hostip/etc in mknfsroot
  * striped executable
  * clients now don't mount the server's /tmp on their /tmp by
    default 
  * Corrected "Continue without Swap" bug in
    /etc/nfsroot/default/etc/boot* scripts.
  
 -- joost witteveen <joost@rulcmc.leidenuniv.nl>  Thu, 31 Oct 1996 22:25:12 +0100

nfsroot (0.2) unstable; urgency=low

  * removed /tftpboot "configfile" dir, as dpkg doesn't like it.
    (refuses to install nfsroot if you don't have /tftpboot already
    on your system)
 -- joost witteveen <joost@rulcmc.leidenuniv.nl>  Mon, 30 Sep 1996 22:31:14 +0200

